%h1
  Your Mind: A User's Guide

%p
  We rely on our minds for almost everything we do, but how much do we actually know about how they work, or how to look after them?
  
%p
  %i
    Your Mind: A User's Guide
  is a new training programme designed to give you the practical knowledge you need to manage your mind more effectively. In just 
  %b
    one hour a month 
  plus some homework and follow-up exercises, we explain essential facts like brain nutrition, mood regulation and stress management, and more advanced topics such as emotional intelligence, decision-making and influence, and help you apply this knowledge to your life and work.

%p
  We offer these programmes to businesses seeking to improve staff health, leadership development and business performance, and we also run occasional public programmes for individuals seeking to get more from their minds. All our training content is based on rigorous psychological and neuroscientific research and delivered by experienced communicators, in an inspiring and engaging style that makes this fascinating material completely relevant to your life and work.

%p
  %i
    "I certainly found the approach novel and informative which is praise indeed having been to so many "stress management sessions"."
  %br
  Dr David Matthews, MB, BS, DRCOG, DOccMed, AFOM, FRCGP, Occupational Physician

